  "caveats": [
    "GEX_z adds incremental fwd-dd info beyond rv (overlap-corrected HAC t=2.86, non-overlap pcorr=0.229, incr R\u00b2=0.0213) \u2014 but incr R\u00b2 is tiny (~2%) and the naive OLS t (~8-11) is overlap-inflated; effect is real but small.",
    "GEX_z and realized vol are themselves correlated (both rise in stress) \u2014 much of GEX's raw fwd-dd corr is shared with vol; partial corr is the honest test.",
    "Standalone 2011-26; trim gate is rebound-safe (trim-only) so it cannot profit from shorting \u2014 it can only reduce drawdown at the cost of upside in calm regimes."
  ],
